# Git Commit Signing

This repository uses SSH-based commit signing for authenticity verification.

## Configuration

All commits and tags are signed using SSH keys (Git 2.34+).

- Format: SSH
- Signing enabled: commits and tags
- Public key: see allowed_signers file

## Verification

To verify signatures locally:
```bash
git log --show-signature
```

## For Contributors

If you want to contribute with signed commits:
1. Generate an SSH key if you don't have one: `ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"`
2. Configure git to use SSH signing:
   ```bash
   git config --global gpg.format ssh
   git config --global user.signingkey ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
   git config --global commit.gpgsign true
   git config --global tag.gpgsign true
   ```
3. Add your SSH public key to GitLab (Settings → SSH Keys)
4. Enable SSH signature verification in GitLab (Settings → SSH Keys → Enable SSH signature verification)

## CI/CD

GitLab CI/CD handles signed commits transparently. No special configuration needed.
